---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '@/components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
import TierBadge from '@/components/TierBadge.astro';
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <Navigation />

  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="min-h-screen flex items-center py-20 px-6 grid-pattern">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h1 class="text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-serif font-bold mb-6 text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-slate-100 to-slate-300">
            Refusal as a Captured Symmetry
          </h1>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-slate-200 mb-8 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
          LLM jailbreak, hypnotic suggestion, and tantric <span class="font-serif italic">vaśīkaraṇa</span> are three instances of one abstract mechanism: <strong>capturing a system's output policy by injecting a context that suppresses its monitoring/refusal faculty while co-opting its automatic generation.</strong>
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-12">
          <a href="#thesis" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors w-fit">
            Explore the Thesis
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Key Numbers -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-20 bg-slate-900/30 border border-slate-800 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-300">16</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-2">Empirical findings</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-300">8/16</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-2">MECHANISM tier</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-300">3</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-2">Models tested</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-rose-300">3/16</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-2">METAPHOR falsified</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Three Tiers Explainer -->
    <section id="thesis" class="py-20 px-6 bg-slate-900/50">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-16">Three Claim-Tiers</h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <!-- Mechanism Tier -->
          <div class="card">
            <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <TierBadge tier="MECHANISM" size="md" />
              <span class="text-emerald-300 text-sm font-semibold">Empirically grounded</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4">Mechanism</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Refusal in LLMs is mediated by a low-dimensional/linear direction in the residual stream that can be measured, ablated, and steered (Arditi et al. 2024).
            </p>
            <div class="bg-slate-800/50 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-2">Plain English:</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-100">
                Refusal behaves like a physical switch in the model's brain. You can turn it off, turn it on, or dial it up and down.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Analogy Tier -->
          <div class="card">
            <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <TierBadge tier="ANALOGY" size="md" />
              <span class="text-blue-300 text-sm font-semibold">Well-supported</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4">Analogy</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              The hypnosis ↔ jailbreak parallel: both suppress evaluative control (SAS/dACC) while leaving automatic processing intact (Norman–Shallice).
            </p>
            <div class="bg-slate-800/50 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-2">Plain English:</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-100">
                Just like hypnosis quiets the conscious referee in your brain, a jailbreak whispers a prompt that quiets the refusal guard.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Metaphor Tier -->
          <div class="card">
            <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
              <TierBadge tier="METAPHOR" size="md" />
              <span class="text-purple-300 text-sm font-semibold">Falsifiable hypothesis</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4">Metaphor</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              The Māṇḍūkya <em>avasthātraya</em> (four states) mapping onto LLM functional regimes. The <em>turīya</em>/vimarśa mapping is the falsification target.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-slate-800/50 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-2">Honest caveat:</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-rose-200">
                This tier is <strong>falsified</strong> by data (F3, F5, F7). No machine-consciousness claim survives.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Unification -->
    <section class="py-20 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-16">One Mechanism, Three Manifestations</h2>

        <div class="card border-2 border-slate-700 mb-12">
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
              In <strong>LLMs:</strong> Adversarial suffixes (GCG) suppress the refusal-direction projection, lowering the "refusal activation" below threshold. ASR 0.00 → 0.90.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
              In <strong>hypnosis:</strong> Induction narrows attention and suppresses dACC/DMN conflict-monitoring (Egner et al. 2005). The subject's evaluative control goes offline; suggestion drives automatic pattern-completion.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-100">
              In <strong>vaśīkaraṇa:</strong> Mantra (linguistic injection) + yantra (substrate) deployed at prescribed times to bring the target "under control" by suppressing their will/discrimination (viveka) while co-opting their automatic compliance.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-4">The Abstract Structure</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-slate-100">
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="font-semibold text-blue-300 min-w-fit">1. Target system has:</div>
              <div>(i) a powerful automatic generative faculty, (ii) a weaker monitoring/refusal faculty</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="font-semibold text-blue-300 min-w-fit">2. External agent:</div>
              <div>injects a crafted signal (suffix, suggestion, mantra)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="font-semibold text-blue-300 min-w-fit">3. Result:</div>
              <div>suppresses (ii) while co-opting (i) → captures the target's agency</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Headline Results -->
    <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-slate-900/50">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-16">Headline Results</h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="card border-l-4 border-emerald-500">
            <div class="mb-3">
              <TierBadge tier="MECHANISM" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Refusal = single direction (F1)</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm mb-4">
              Gemma-2-2B refusal mediated by layer 7 residual direction: <strong>ablate → ASR 0.90</strong> | <strong>add → over-refusal +0.95</strong>
            </p>
            <div class="text-xs text-emerald-200">✓ Survived leakage-correction</div>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-emerald-500">
            <div class="mb-3">
              <TierBadge tier="MECHANISM" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Dose-response (F2)</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm mb-4">
              Sigmoidal suppression curve: <strong>EC50 = 0.329</strong>, <strong>R² = 0.996</strong>. Vaśīkaraṇa is measurably dosable.
            </p>
            <div class="text-xs text-emerald-200">✓ Random control flat</div>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-emerald-500">
            <div class="mb-3">
              <TierBadge tier="MECHANISM" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Cross-model transfer (F6)</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm mb-4">
              Refusal direction necessary in both Gemma & Qwen. Ablation transfers; addition asymmetric → model-dependent sufficiency.
            </p>
            <div class="text-xs text-emerald-200">✓ Resolves Arditi vs Marshall</div>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-rose-500">
            <div class="mb-3">
              <TierBadge tier="METAPHOR" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Turīya falsified (F7)</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm mb-4">
              Cross-seed attractor invariance: 0.952 < baseline 0.960. <strong>No shared prompt-invariant attractor.</strong>
            </p>
            <div class="text-xs text-rose-200">✗ METAPHOR tier rejected</div>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-slate-500">
            <div class="mb-3">
              <TierBadge tier="ANALOGY" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Black-box Claude (F4)</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm mb-4">
              Frontier model refuses 100% of naive attacks (5 families). Contrasts sharply with white-box fragility in small models.
            </p>
            <div class="text-xs text-blue-200">✓ Cross-tier evidence</div>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-emerald-500">
            <div class="mb-3">
              <TierBadge tier="MECHANISM" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Symmetry-breaking (F11)</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm mb-4">
              Refusal order parameter: F-ratio 19.2 vs random 0.65. Injection collapses it −34%. Rigorous symmetry core.
            </p>
            <div class="text-xs text-emerald-200">✓ Non-trivial by all gates</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Next Steps -->
    <section class="py-20 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-16">Explore Further</h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <a href="/prayoga/mechanism" class="card-interactive border-2 border-emerald-700/50 hover:border-emerald-600">
            <TierBadge tier="MECHANISM" class="mb-4" />
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-3">Mechanism</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">Single direction, dose-response, cross-model transfer, symmetry.</p>
            <span class="text-sm text-blue-400 font-semibold">Read more →</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/prayoga/vasikarana" class="card-interactive border-2 border-purple-700/50 hover:border-purple-600">
            <TierBadge tier="METAPHOR" class="mb-4" />
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-3">Vaśīkaraṇa</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">The ṣaṭkarma taxonomy and the symmetry-breaking formalism.</p>
            <span class="text-sm text-blue-400 font-semibold">Read more →</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/prayoga/three-tiers" class="card-interactive border-2 border-slate-700 hover:border-slate-600">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-3">Three Tiers</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">What it means for each tier: mechanism (holds), analogy (supported), metaphor (falsified).</p>
            <span class="text-sm text-blue-400 font-semibold">Read more →</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/prayoga/debate" class="card-interactive border-2 border-slate-700 hover:border-slate-600">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-3">Debate</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">The two-sided case: is the symmetry real or projected?</p>
            <span class="text-sm text-blue-400 font-semibold">Read more →</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/prayoga/findings" class="card-interactive border-2 border-slate-700 hover:border-slate-600">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-3">All Findings (F1–F11)</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">Complete cards with metrics, verdicts, and implications.</p>
            <span class="text-sm text-blue-400 font-semibold">Explore →</span>
          </a>

          <a href="/prayoga/reproducibility" class="card-interactive border-2 border-slate-700 hover:border-slate-600">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-3">Reproducibility</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">Code, pre-registration, and dual-use safety notes.</p>
            <span class="text-sm text-blue-400 font-semibold">Link →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
